  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Head of Instruction & Material Development",
  "description": "<p><strong>Instructional &amp; Materials Development:</strong></p>\n<p>·       Lead the development and revision of instructional materials, ensuring content is up-to-date and aligned with academic standards and institutional objectives</p>\n<p>·       Develop and implement teaching strategies that promote active learning and critical thinking, catering to diverse learner needs.</p>\n<p>·       Evaluate and review the effectiveness of educational materials through assessments and feedback from instructors and students, making necessary adjustments.</p>\n<p>·       Work closely with teaching staff to ensure materials and strategies are effectively applied in classrooms and address any challenges they may face.</p>\n<p>·       Train future franchisees in instructional practices and material development</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Centre Operations Management:</strong></p>\n<p>·       Oversee the department's budget, ensuring efficient allocation of resources for the centre operations.</p>\n<p>·       In the event of staff shortages, the role includes providing support by covering essential duties as needed. Additionally, the position involves taking on teaching responsibilities when required.</p>\n<p>·       Develop and implement processes that assist the day-to-day operations.</p>\n<p>·       Responsible for overseeing the daily operations of the centre and effectively managing the team of instructors to ensure smooth functioning and high-quality service delivery.</p>\n<p>·       Drive sales growth for the centre by implementing effective strategies to attract new clients and retain existing ones, ultimately contributing to the centre’s overall revenue and success.</p>\n<p>·       Lead the setting up new centres, overseeing all aspects of operational planning, logistics, and staffing to ensure a smooth and successful launch.</p>\n<p>·       Develop SOP for setting up new centre with the goal of using these guidelines for future franchise training and expansion.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Compliance &amp; Quality Assurance:</strong></p>\n<p>·       Ensure that all instructional materials meet regulatory, accreditation, and institutional standards for quality and compliance.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Stakeholder Communication:</strong></p>\n<p>·       Collaborate with school leadership, parents, and external stakeholders to ensure the continuous improvement and relevance of instructional materials.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Other Duties</strong></p>\n<p>·       Perform any additional duties as assigned by management</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirement</strong>: Must have knowledge of Maths at PSLE level</p>\n<p><strong>Work Schedule:</strong> 5-day work week (including weekends); required to work on Saturdays and Sundays</p>",
